ital artery","Ophthalmic artery","Anterior ethmoidal artery","Central retinal artery"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eophthalmic artery\u003C/strong\u003E is the first branch of the internal carotid artery after it exits the cavernous sinus. It enters the orbit through the optic canal with the optic nerve to supply the eye and surrounding structures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are all branches of the ophthalmic artery:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elacrimal artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the lacrimal gland and eyelids\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esupraorbital artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the forehead and scalp\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior ethmoidal artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the anterior ethmoidal air cells and anterior nasal cavity\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecentral retinal artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the inner retinal layers\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding this vascular anatomy is important as the ophthalmic artery and its branches provide the main blood supply to the eye and orbital contents.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The ophthalmic artery is the first branch of the internal carotid artery.","The ophthalmic artery supplies the eye and surrounding structures."],"references":["Charlick M, Das JM. Anatomy, Head and Neck: Internal Carotid Arteries. [Updated 2023 Jul 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK556061/","Netter, F. H.. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: Classic Regional Approach-Ebook. 2022. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50647"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14334"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"